Jeanette Chabalala, News24Four bags of Mandrax tablets. (SAPS) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Grahamstown &ndash; Eastern Cape police have arrested two people and seized R400&nbsp;000 worth of mandrax tablets while conducting a vehicle check on Wednesday afternoon, police said.&nbsp; The two, a man and a woman aged, 50 and 25 where stopped at Raglan road in Grahamstown, Captain Mali Govender said. &nbsp;On searching the vehicle, a bag containing four packets filled with mandrax tablets was found. The suspects will appear in the Grahamstown Magistrate&rsquo;s Court soon for possession of drugs. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.